<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/478: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-02T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                            1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        August 4, 4.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>108. Colombian Foreign Office and press announce that treaty will be
                                discussed by Senate in open session Tuesday the 5th instant. I
                                respectfully suggest that steps should be taken to avoid discussion
                                of confidential agreement and note of Colombian Government
                                signifying acceptance of modifications which I obtained for
                                information of committee only. President in agreeing to publication
                                of the note stipulated that it would be subsidiary [to] ratification
                                in [<hi rend="italic">of</hi>] treaty.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>